        <body>       
                
                <pb n="1"/>
                <p>Omer 47<lb/>
                Boston Sivan 3 5647<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. S. Morais<lb/>
                My very dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I have forwarded<lb/> this day by Adam&#39;s Express<lb/> to you a Scroll of the<lb/> Holy Law only finished<lb/> in this City yesterday it<lb/> was commenced in Wilna<lb/> Russia&#44; &#38; the scribe finished<lb/> the fifth book here.  I know<lb/> both father for some time &#38;<lb/> he is an <sic>excepitinal</sic> good<lb/> man.  I purchased one for<lb/> our own shule&#44; these two<lb/> <sic>scolls</sic> I bought in Sacred<lb/> Memory of my darling Angel<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Wife now if you will take<lb/> the scroll I have sent you<lb/> and <hi rend="underline">present it to your<lb/> Congregation&#44; conjointly<lb/> with my dear son &#38; daughter<lb/> &#38; son &#38; self in Gratitude</hi><lb/> to your congregation for your<lb/> noble deed in hastening &#38;<lb/> officiating at my poor<lb/> wife funeral&#44; &#38; if your<lb/> congregation will so record<lb/> in their books&#44; &#38; three times<lb/> a year when prayers are<lb/> said for the souls of the<lb/> departed her name should<lb/> be remembered. the cover &#38;<lb/> mappa I should like<lb/> returned when I send a<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>a new&#44; or if you could get a handsome<lb/> white satin &#38; colomed&#91;&#63;&#93; one made in Philadelphia<lb/> We will pay for it.  Secondly I have sent<lb/> from New York 50 small Hebrew prayer<lb/> Books which please donate in our joint<lb/> names to the Foster Home&#44; &#38; the best charitable<lb/> societies divided as you deem fit &#38; also<lb/> 2 sewing machines&#44; send where they will<lb/> do the most good &#40;I hope you will use the scroll<lb/> at the Holy festival Sunday&#41; &#38; now my dear Mr. Morais we have sent<lb/> for your very kind acceptance according<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>to my promise a silver Kidish Cap &#38;<lb/> Stand &#38; may the God of Israel spare<lb/> your life for very many many years<lb/> to enjoy the Sabbath &#38; Holy festivals<lb/> &#38; in remembrance of the sad duties you<lb/> performed over my pure darling blessed wife<lb/> God rest her soul with the kindest<lb/> wishes &#38; regards in which my darling daughter<lb/> &#38; son join to all dear to you I am<lb/> wishing you good<lb/> yourself<lb/> Yours very faithfully<lb/> Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="5"/>
            <p>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                P.a.<lb/></p>
            </body>
